      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DURAN PANTERA (2) sprung the lids and led throughout to score by 7 lengths (30.39) at Gawler in Grade 6. Failed to fire only run here. Boasts a strong record from this draw with two wins and two minor placings from five starts. Looks the one to beat. ENHANCE (6) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by 1.5 lengths at this track in a handy 25.76 beating Adhana Martina. Still to record a win from this draw but has never missed the frame in three starts. One of main contenders. ADHANA MADI (1) turned spotting a big start finishing fourth (31.30) last time in a Grade 6 at Angle Park. Form at the trip sound including three wins. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. ADHANA HENRY (8) can improve on an unplaced run here last time out.",
